@using MudBlazor;

<MudDialog>
    <DialogContent>
        The Steak Grilling Guide app is intended to help grill your steaks the way you want them. Our first goal was simple: how can someone cook multiple steaks and have them finish at the same time.
        <br/>
        <br/>
        The timing information this app uses comes from <MudLink Href="https://www.omahasteaks.com/blog/grill-the-perfect-steak/">Omaha Steaks guide to grilling your perfect steak</MudLink>. This resource is a great
        way for beginners to learn the basics of grilling your own steak. Omaha's' table for thickness and center cook is what this app will use to determine how to grill your steaks. 
        <br/>
        <br/>
        If you are not a beginner and simply want a timer, the Steak Grilling Guide will grow to help meet your needs. Eventually this app will contain ways for you to customize the amount of time you want for
        your steaks. The end goal is much like our first: the ability to cook steaks how you want them with the help of an app that will notify you when to place, flip, and take off your steaks. 
        <br/>
        <br/>
        We are always open to feedback and suggestions, if you would like to reach out to us you can send an email to <MudLink Href="mailto:steakgrillingguide@gmail.com">steakgrillingguide@gmail.com</MudLink>
    </DialogContent>
    <DialogActions>
        <MudButton Variant="Variant.Outlined" OnClick="Submit">Close</MudButton>
    </DialogActions>
</MudDialog>